First of all, thank you for creating this content. It must have taken a lot of effort to put this together. 
Warning for beginners: I am a complete beginner to yoga practices and came to this 30 day yoga practice on many recommandations that stated this would be an easy place to get started. I must admit that the practices in and of themselves feel very nice, realtively easy to perform and I enjoyed myself whilst performing them. BUT, the almost constant usage of what I can only describe as confusing and too imaginative language makes it really hard to follow the instructions of the teacher. We are constantly asked to do things where I had  no idea what she was talking about inbetween the clear instructins of move this, stretch that, center this. I assume that this type of terminoligy is generally used in yoga practices, because yoga is not just about stretching, but also about connecting with yourself. For a beginner, though, it becomes really difficult to follow the instructions without constantly breaking form to look at the screen. For beginners I would suggest that you watch the whole video before you actually start the practice. Unless things like "allow your breath to make room towards your hip" (exagerated, but if you watch the video you will understand what i mean) are things that will not break your concentration.
